set.bowdlerize: (v.) to remove offensive material from a text, making it weaker or less effective.
set.cognate: (adj.) similar or related; [of a word] having the same derivation as another word
set.doggerel: (n.) a comic verse in irregular rhythm; a words that are badly written or expressed.
set.paradigm: (n.) a typical example or pattern of something; a model.
set.parlance: (n.) a particular way of speaking, especially one common to those with a particular job or interest.
set.pastoral: (adj.) [of a piece of land] used for sheep or cattle; [in the Chrisitan Church] concerning spiritual guidance; (n.) a work of literature portraying an idealized version of country life.
set.protagonist: (n.) the main character in a work of fiction; an advocate of a particular idea
set.vernacular: (n.) the language spoken by ordinary people in a particular region; architecture that is domestic and functional rather than public and monumental
set.accede: (v.) agree to a demand, request, or treaty; assume an office or position.
set.concession: (n.) something that is given up in order to end a disagreement, or the act of giving it up; an admission
set.defray: (v.) to provide money to pay for somthing
set.infraction: (n.) the violation of a law or agreement
set.intercession: (n.) intervention on the behalf of someone else; praying for someone
set.precedent: (n.) a past event that can be used as an example for similar situations.
set.refractory: (adj.) stubborn or unmanageable; resistant to a process
